001package org.biopax.paxtools.impl.level3;
002
003import org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.*;
004import org.biopax.paxtools.util.IllegalBioPAXArgumentException;
005
006public class GeneticInteractionImpl extends InteractionImpl
007        implements GeneticInteraction
008{
009        private PhenotypeVocabulary phenotype;
010
011    private Score interactionScore;
012        
013        public GeneticInteractionImpl() {
014        }
015
016        public Class<? extends GeneticInteraction> getModelInterface()
017        {
018                return GeneticInteraction.class;
019        }
020
021        public PhenotypeVocabulary getPhenotype()
022    {
023        return phenotype;
024    }
025
026    public void setPhenotype(PhenotypeVocabulary phenotype)
027    {
028        this.phenotype = phenotype;
029    }
030
031    public Score getInteractionScore()
032    {
033        return interactionScore;
034    }
035
036    public void setInteractionScore(Score interactionScore)
037    {
038        this.interactionScore = interactionScore;
039    }
040
041    @Override
042    public void addParticipant(Entity aParticipant) {
043        if (aParticipant instanceof Gene)
044            super.addParticipant(aParticipant);
045        else
046            throw new IllegalBioPAXArgumentException(
047                "GeneticInteraction can only have Gene participants (at least two).");
048    }
049}
